---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Music - Pete Cohen"
  description="Pete Cohen's music career - from Sodastream to Smith & Cohen and beyond"
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">Music</h1>
      <div class="prose text-lg text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
        <p>
          I started playing piano at 7, taught by my aunty. Then at 11, I was walking down the hallway at school and was commanded to put out my hands. I was summarily told I'd be playing double bass (even though I didn't know what it was). The rest is basically history.
        </p>
        <p>
          That moment of the double bass finding me is a recurring theme of my musical journey. More than just a calling, it feels more like a destiny, and one that I have limited control over. Right now I'm thankful for my relationship with it - much more than a hobby, but not something I have to suffer or resent.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Key Resources -->
    <section class="mb-16 p-8 border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Key Resources</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">
            <a
              href="https://www.discogs.com/artist/480650-Pete-Cohen"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]"
            >
              Discogs Profile →
            </a>
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Complete discography of all releases I've played on</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">
            <a
              href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sodastream_(band)"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]"
            >
              Sodastream on Wikipedia →
            </a>
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">The band that shaped my musical journey</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">
          <a
            href="https://ameliema.home.xs4all.nl/sodastream/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]"
          >
            The Sodastream Archive →
          </a>
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">An incredible and precious archive of our work - the most complete I am aware of</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Brief Musical Journey -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="prose max-w-none">
        <p>
          I was classically trained on double bass during my school years, but I never really had the chops or the aspiration to pursue a conservatory musical education. In my teens I discovered electric bass, and I remember hearing the riff from Smoke on the Water at the music store - it was like a mainline injection of rock'n'roll into my veins. I would go on to spend countless hours noodling on that bass in my bedroom throughout my teens.
        </p>
        <p>
          Shortly after high school I started gigging in Perth - the most isolated capital city in the world really felt like it at the time, but it had the magic of being its own microcosm. One of my favourite bands to watch was Thermos Cardy, and when their bass player left the band, I was invited to join. That was the beginning of Sodastream.
        </p>
        <p>
          Karl and I have maintained a wonderful friendship and musical partnership for almost 30 years now. We have travelled the world extensively together and have supported each other as we've established our families and lives. I feel incredibly fortunate that we get to keep making music together, and not just in a nostalgic kind of way, but rather one that is always seeking out and opening up new fronts.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="/blog" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">Read my full musical story →</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Bands -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Main Projects</h2>

      <div class="space-y-12">
        <!-- Smith & Cohen -->
        <div class="border-l-4 border-[var(--color-accent)] pl-6">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-4">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Smith & Cohen</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">2017 – Present</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-4">
            The continuation of our musical partnership under a new name. Released our album <em>Half Life</em> in 2025.
          </p>
          <div class="flex gap-4 flex-wrap">
            <a
              href="https://bio.site/smithandcohen"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="px-4 py-2 border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg hover:border-[var(--color-accent)] hover:text-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors text-sm"
            >
              Bio →
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Releases:</h4>
            <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] space-y-1">
              <li>• <em>Half Life</em> (2025)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Sodastream -->
        <div class="border-l-4 border-[var(--color-accent)] pl-6">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-4">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Sodastream</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">1996 – 2020</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-4">
            The band that defined my musical career. Started when I joined what was Thermos Cardy, we went on to tour internationally and release numerous albums over more than two decades.
          </p>
          <div class="flex gap-4 flex-wrap">
            <a
              href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sodastream_(band)"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="px-4 py-2 border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg hover:border-[var(--color-accent)] hover:text-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors text-sm"
            >
              Wikipedia →
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://ameliema.home.xs4all.nl/sodastream/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="px-4 py-2 border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg hover:border-[var(--color-accent)] hover:text-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors text-sm"
            >
              Archive →
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Selected Releases:</h4>
            <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] space-y-1">
              <li>• <em>Letter From Melbourne</em> (2020)</li>
              <li>• <em>Little By Little</em> (2017)</li>
              <li>• <em>Reservations</em> (2006)</li>
              <li>• <em>A Minor Revival</em> (2003)</li>
              <li>• <em>The Hill For Company</em> (2001)</li>
              <li>• <em>Looks Like A Russian</em> (2000)</li>
              <li>• <em>Enjoy</em> (2001)</li>
              <li>• <em>Turnstyle</em> (1999)</li>
              <li>• <em>Practical Footwear</em> (1998)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Other Main Projects -->
        <div class="border-l-4 border-[var(--color-border)] pl-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Other Projects</h3>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
            <div>Khancoban</div>
            <div>Lee Memorial</div>
            <div>RPM Trio</div>
            <div>The Best Friends Group</div>
            <div>The Purple Stripes</div>
            <div>Lunacy</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Session & Collaborative Work -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Session & Collaborative Work</h2>
      <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-6">
        Along the way, I'm honoured to have had the opportunity to play with many bands as a guest musician, and sometimes as a member. These moments of connection are precious to me, and transcend a mere friendship.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <!-- Architecture in Helsinki -->
        <div class="border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Architecture in Helsinki</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-3">2005</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] space-y-1">
            <li>• <em>In Case We Die</em> (2005)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Luluc -->
        <div class="border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Luluc</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-3">2008</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] space-y-1">
            <li>• <em>Dear Hamlyn</em> (2008)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Machine Translations -->
        <div class="border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Machine Translations</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-3">2004</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] space-y-1">
            <li>• <em>Venus Traps Fly</em> (2004)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Clare Bowditch and the Feeding Set -->
        <div class="border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Clare Bowditch and the Feeding Set</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-3">2005</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] space-y-1">
            <li>• <em>What Was Left</em></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- The Lucksmiths -->
        <div class="border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">The Lucksmiths</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-3">1999-2001</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] space-y-1">
            <li>• <em>Staring At The Sky</em> (1999)</li>
            <li>• <em>North American Summer 2001</em> (2001)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Richard Easton and the Rhumba Decoy -->
        <div class="border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Richard Easton and the Rhumba Decoy</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-3">1999</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] space-y-1">
            <li>• <em>Tallulah O'Shay</em> (1999)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Because of Ghosts -->
        <div class="border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Because of Ghosts</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-3">2006</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] space-y-1">
            <li>• <em>The Tomorrow We Were Promised Yesterday</em> (2006)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Mountains in the Sky -->
        <div class="border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Mountains in the Sky</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-3">2008</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] space-y-1">
            <li>• <em>Electron Suite</em> (2008)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Emma Heeney -->
        <div class="border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Emma Heeney</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-3">2014</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] space-y-1">
            <li>• <em>After The Fireworks</em> (2014)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Heathcote Blue -->
        <div class="border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Heathcote Blue</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-3">2017</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] space-y-1">
            <li>• <em>Stray Dog Daily</em> (2017)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Oliver Mann -->
        <div class="border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Oliver Mann</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-3">2005</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] space-y-1">
            <li>• <em>Oliver Mann Sings</em> (2005)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Brea Acton -->
        <div class="border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Brea Acton</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-3">2015</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] space-y-1">
            <li>• <em>We Are Listening</em> (2015)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Additional Session Work -->
      <div class="mt-8 pt-8 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Additional Session Work</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-3 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
          <div>The Guild League</div>
          <div>The Smallgoods</div>
          <div>The High Barnets</div>
          <div>Comaneci</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Notable Compilations -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Notable Compilations</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div class="border-l-2 border-[var(--color-border)] pl-4">
          <div class="font-semibold">Banter (A Candle Records Collection)</div>
          <div class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Various (2000)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-2 border-[var(--color-border)] pl-4">
          <div class="font-semibold">Feast</div>
          <div class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Various (2002)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-2 border-[var(--color-border)] pl-4">
          <div class="font-semibold">I Am A Cold Rock. I Am Dull Grass.</div>
          <div class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Tribute to Will Oldham (2004)</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Closing -->
    <section class="prose max-w-none">
      <p class="text-lg">
        I hope that this account of my musical journey is only half done, and that there are many more chapters to add.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
